22 Section 3. KRS 314.042 is amended to read as follows:
23 (1) An applicant for licensure to practice as an advanced practice registered nurse shall
24 file with the board a written application for licensure and submit evidence, verified
25 by oath, that the applicant:
26 (a) Has completed an education program that prepares the registered nurse for
27 one (1) of four (4) APRN roles that has been accredited by a national nursing
